                <div id="the-challenge">
                  <div class="p-work-overview__container">
                    <h3 class="p-work-overview--amity p-work-overview__title" id="the-challenge">The Challenge</h3>
                    <div class="p-work-overview__description"> The challenge was to design a complex B2B platform for
                      remote control and monitoring of stoves in living facilities for
                      elderly and disabled individuals. The platform needed to allow for easy control of stoves by both
                      residents through the
                      app and maintenance staff, while balancing the need for safety, convenience, and independence. The
                      key objective was to
                      provide a solution that allows users to switch off, block, and monitor the status of stoves
                      remotely.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div id="the-solution">
                  <div class="p-work-overview__container">
                    <h3 class="p-work-overview--amity p-work-overview__title" id="the-solution">The Solution</h3>
                    <div class="p-work-overview__description">To meet the client's request, a comprehensive B2B
                      platform, Amity, was designed to control stoves in living facilities
                      for elderly and disabled individuals. The design process involved a thorough specification
                      discovery, user flow
                      analysis, information architecture, wireframing, and visual design (UI) to ensure an intuitive and
                      user-friendly
                      solution. The platform, connected to the Ome app, allows residents to control their own stoves,
                      while maintenance staff
                      can monitor and adjust stove usage through the Amity web platform. The end result is a solution
                      that strikes a balance
                      between safety, convenience, and independence for all users, providing a comfortable and secure
                      living environment for
                      elderly and disabled individuals in these facilities.
                    </div>
                    <video autoplay muted loop playsinline width="955" height="716" data-scroll data-scroll-speed="-1">
                      <!-- width="1632" height="1020"  -->
