                    <h3 class="p-work-overview--amity p-work-overview__title" id="results-and-takeaways">Results and
                      <span style="color: #000;">takeaways</span>
                    </h3>
                    <div class="p-work-overview__description">
                      <p>The Amity project was a success, resulting in the
                        successful launch of the MVP version of the platform. Our team worked
                        diligently to bring the client's vision to life, and the result is a platform that is both
                        functional and user-friendly.
                        The platform offers robust features and capabilities, delivering on the needs of the end-users
                        and
                        providing a seamless
                        experience for maintenance staff.</p>
                      <p> One of the key takeaways from this project is the importance of collaboration and open
                        communication with the client. By
                        working closely with the client and ensuring their input was incorporated into the design, we
                        were
                        able to deliver a
                        product that exceeded their expectations. The user-centered design approach, which prioritized
                        the
                        needs of the
                        end-users, also played a critical role in the success of the project.</p>
                      <p>In conclusion, the Amity project was a great success and a testament to the power of teamwork
                        and
                        user-centered design.
                        The platform is now live and making a positive impact on the lives of elderly people and people
                        with some disorders. We
                        are proud to have been a part of this project and are excited to see what the future holds for
                        Amity.</p>
                      <h4>Key takeaways from this project are:</h4>
                      <div class="p-work-overview__description"></div>
                      <ul>
                        <li>User testing doesn't end after development. Design
                          is a constant iteration of improving the experience for the end user.
                          Always find ways to collect and listen to your user's feedback.
                        </li>
                        <li>Involve engineering upfront. This helps to reduce any rework later on as an understanding
                          of the technical limitations
                          upfront will help to inform your design strategy.</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
